cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically the problem of structure from motion (SfM). Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The use of physical constraints and iterative optimization methods aligns with the Robotics sub-category (cs.RO). Finally, the paper also discusses geometric consistency, which is relevant to the Graphics sub-category (cs.GR).
